where or dont want my cut of a 50 plat split, then your the one with the problem.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If a person tells of there accomplishments and others take this as bragging aswell, this completely mistifies me. Bragging is when somone doesnt shut up about what they have done. Yes a true veteran will always have tales of those fights and times they are proud of what they have been able to do. Most of it though is either they got lucky and figured out somthing or they just got lucky. Yes to give a background, ive 1 tanked vishmitar on a few occassions, ive 1 tanked tunat on a few occassions. Ive never sucessefully 1 tanked OMM nor has my guild killed OMM. But it doesnt really matter either way, because even though i lived in those situations i possibly shouldnt I dont take full credit, I have **SMURF** good clerics, awesome shamans and  uber guildies and enchanters to let me not have to worry about my surroundings as much as others might. I personally am **SMURF** lucky to have had the chance to be guilded with people who show skill and grace at there accomplishments. People who have level heads in bad situations, Yes there were times i felt we were going to wipe, alot of times you say POWER THRU, in raid just to give them focus when times get bad. Other times you say were going to wipe but god dam* lets make  him earn killing us. Luck and skill are brothers, some people never realize this others do.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So drop the elitist tagging of every person that doesnt want to group, or split because sometimes, they just have no reason to xp at all, I know many that are max aa and maxxed bank aa. They play merely for the enjoyment of the group at this stage, for the fun of it all.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Lord Chriten Dathemiere&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Dark bane of saryn&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
